items.caption: Mapping of image, color, and LED animation to respective status

SOC (State of Charge) and target SOC are unfortunately not provided by Type 2 wallboxes. Those who want to use this display must obtain the values elsewhere (API connection to the car, etc.). The user must implement their own logic to control the display of SOC and target SOC. A Boolean variable can be selected for showing or hiding. If false, the SOC or the charging target is hidden; if true, it is shown. The target SOC is only displayed when the SOC is also displayed.
